Deprecated API

Contents

  • Deprecated Exceptions
  • Deprecated Methods
  • Deprecated Constructors
  • Deprecated Exceptions 
    Exceptions and Description
    oracle.cloudstorage.ftm.exception.NotEnoughSpaceInTempDir
    As of release 2.1
  • Deprecated Methods 
    Method and Description
    oracle.cloudstorage.ftm.FileTransferAuth.getPassword()
    For security reasons, this method is deprecated as of release 2.1. Use FileTransferAuth.getAuthPassword() instead.
    oracle.cloudstorage.ftm.FileTransferManagerConfig.getTempDirPath()
    As of release 2.1, temporary directory is not required for transferring files.

    Returns temporary directory path location used for transferring large files.
    oracle.cloudstorage.ftm.FileTransferAuth.setPassword(String)
    For security reasons, this method is deprecated as of release 2.1. Use FileTransferAuth.setAuthPassword(char[]) instead.
    oracle.cloudstorage.ftm.FileTransferManagerConfig.setTempDirPath(String)
    As of release 2.1, temporary directory is not required for transferring files.

    Sets temporary directory path location used for transferring large files.
  • Deprecated Constructors 
    Constructor and Description
    oracle.cloudstorage.ftm.FileTransferAuth(String, String, String, String, String)
    As of release 2.1. Instead use the constructor that takes the password as a character array.
    oracle.cloudstorage.ftm.FileTransferManagerConfig(int, int, long, String)
    Instead use the constructor with no arguments. As of release 2.1, the parameter tempDirPath is not supported.
